==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Passover
<hw>Pass"o`ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pass</ets> +
<ets>over</ets>. See Pasch.]</ety> <fld>(Jewish Antiq.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A feast of the Jews, instituted to commemorate the
sparing of the Hebrews in Egypt, when God, smiting the firstborn of the
Egyptians, <xex>passed over</xex> the houses of the Israelites which
were marked with the blood of a lamb.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
sacrifice offered at the feast of the passover; the paschal lamb.</def>
<rj><au>Ex. xii.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pass-parole</ent>⟦br⟧
